CTOX repository notice

This repository contains first-party CTOX code plus integrated hard forks
and integrated per-model inference trees.

Primary integrated source trees:

- src/harness
  Derived from https://github.com/openai/codex
  Upstream license: Apache-2.0
  Integrated into CTOX as a source-owned hard fork and driven in-process
  by CTOX's agent turn loop. Previously lived at src/inference/.

- src/inference/models/<model>/
  Per-model self-contained inference crates. Each crate carries its own
  Rust inference code plus its own vendored kernel source (CUDA/Metal)
  in-tree. Upstream vendored kernel provenance is pinned per crate in
  `vendor/*.version` files. No code is shared across model crates.

The previously-carried Candle-based `tools/model-runtime/` subtree has
been retired.

- tools/web-stack/assets/humanlike.mjs
  Behavioral primitives (mouse Bezier curves, typing latency model with
  nearby-key mistypes, three-phase burst-wheel scrolling, actionability
  gating) are reimplemented in JavaScript from the open-source Python
  wrapper of https://github.com/CloakHQ/CloakBrowser (MIT, Copyright
  CloakHQ). Only the wrapper algorithms are ported; the patched-Chromium
  binary is not used and not redistributed.

- runtime/browser/interactive-reference/ (operator workspace)
  CTOX drives Chromium through Patchright
  (https://github.com/Kaliiiiiiiiii-Vinyzu/patchright-nodejs, Apache 2.0),
  a drop-in Playwright fork that patches Runtime.enable, Console.enable,
  and source-URL CDP leaks. The package is installed at runtime into the
  operator workspace via `npx patchright install chromium` and not
  bundled into the CTOX distribution.

The root LICENSE applies to first-party CTOX repository code unless an
integrated source subtree or file states otherwise.
